Yep. Time/opportunity cost includes cross chain attacks.
Agreed - partially my point is that time/opportunity floats the value purely beyond ETH+ETC
Value of DS accounts may be greater than ETH+ETC (zero sum). They are akin to a one-time-use lottery ticket + futures market of ETH+ETC.
As more post-fork ETH/ETC is mined, accounts that can be cleanly double-spent across both chains will see value diverge from ETH/ETC.
Further, economically, pre-fork ETH (PFETH) is not certain to be ETH+ETC. Flexibility can add value. Not zero sum.
I was making the specific technical point of pre-fork ETH accounts that can be double spent, versus post-fork non-DS accts.
Balance system (vs. UTXO) mitigates this somewhat, depending on how value was stored (account reuse etc.)
Pre-fork keys/mined coins that can be redeemed on both chains have more value than post-fork mined coins.
